    • Field Detail

      • PROPERTY_KIND_STRING

        static final java.lang.String PROPERTY_KIND_STRING
        A property kind for string properties. This is the default property kind.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • PROPERTY_KIND_READONLY_STRING

        static final java.lang.String PROPERTY_KIND_READONLY_STRING
        A property kind for readonly string properties. The intention is that there is no way in the UI to edit, rename, or delete readonly properties. These properties must be created and manipulated programatically.
        Since:
        0.6.1
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

        java.lang.String getKind()

      • isWellKnown

        boolean isWellKnown()
        The isWellKnown attribute specifies whether the name and description attributes of the given property are fixed (non-editable) The default value is false meaning that all attributes of generic properties are, by default, editable. For well known properties whose property name and description should remain constant, this value should be set to true. The default value is false.
        Returns:
        Whether this property is well known.
        Since:
        0.9.5
